                "message": "Escape github label name\n\n... by sending it through the environment.\n\nThis is a potential \"code injection via template expansion\" that\nzizmor (zizmor.sh) identifies.  It does identify a few others\ntoo however they're all from input variables that we directly\ncontrol (e.g. `${{ inputs.compiler }}`) so I believe are genuinely fine,\nwhile this one is from something somewhat external.\nI don't think it's a real issue\nbut it seemed like it might be worth fixing while I was looking\nat it",
